.314105104/asset/images/105104fig20.jpeg" height="1024" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig20" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 20</span> Occluded TIPS in a 48-year-old man with cirrhosis and recurrent variceal bleeding. Oblique Doppler sonogram shows complete absence of flow within the TIPS (arrows), a finding indicative of occlusion.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.314105104&amp;id=fig20">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig21a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.314105104/asset/images/105104fig21a.jpeg" height="1280" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 21a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.314105104&amp;id=fig21a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig21b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.314105104/asset/images/105104fig21b.jpeg" height="1280" width="1278" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 21b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.314105104&amp;id=fig21b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">1.</div><div id="r1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Marks C. Developmental basis of the portal venous system. <em>Am J Surg</em> 1969;117(5):671–681.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/0002-9610(69)90404-